Our Company

PVH has grown to become one of the largest global apparel companies. Our growth profile has been achieved through organic growth, as well as a number of successful acquisitions that have redefined our identity, performance and long-term growth potential. These acquisitions include Calvin Klein in 2003, Tommy Hilfiger in 2010, and Warnaco in 2013. As our company has grown and transformed, our focus remains on global expansion and brand development, while staying true to our core values.










Our Core Values

Our core values shape our culture at PVH — individuality, partnership, passion, integrity and accountability. We live by our core values — they inspire us, and we believe that these qualities, as practiced by our associates, are what will help us grow our businesses into the future.










Leadership

We believe that our strong corporate leadership will drive sustainable long-term global growth while creating positive financial returns for our stockholders. Our executive team embodies our core values, which are an inherent part of our corporate culture. 










Business Groups

We leverage our best-in-class global infrastructure, supply chain, brand-focused management and marketing teams to support each of our three business groups — Calvin Klein, Tommy Hilfiger and Heritage Brands — through a strategic combination of wholesale, retail, digital commerce and licensing operations.





