Design Your Future at PVH
Creative Product Development Coordinator, Knitwear - CALVIN KLEIN
Facilitate the creative process by accurately sharing flow information with the Italian Product Development team in order to ensure the coherence and the continuity of the designer’s message
PRIMARY RESPONSIBILITIES/ACCOUNTABILITIES OF THE JOB:

Support designer team in material research and developing knit swatches
Coordinate with suppliers to receive yarn color cards and samples (logistics) on time and  sharing the information with Italian Product Development Team
Create Cutting Tickets in PM WEB.
Coordinate with NY Product Development team to cut tickets for knitwear prototypes to pass to NY Atelier and share information immediately with the Italian Product Development Team
Update the Italian Product Development Team about costing of developments made in NY for budget control (ownership Italian Product Development)
With input from the designer, purchase materials for prototypes and samples while also communicating to Italian Product Development team
Trims development when specifically requested for Knitwear
Maintain a catalogue of all the seasonal materials and samples for the design team to utilize
Sketch coordination (styles codes, catalogue , overview, updating)
Document preparation for prototypes, samples and creative launch (sketches, yarn, colors)
Accurately and completely update documentation and any other necessary information that must be shared with the Italian Product Development team in order to streamline all the following processes: costing; merchandising consistency, marketing operation, industrialization and pre-start-up activities for production
Support the Product Development team with the logistics of prototype and sample deliveries
Supports the designers and the product team during fittings

QUALIFICATIONS & EXPERIENCE:
Experience:   2/3 years of experience as product developer is needed.
Education:   Degree in design / product development.
Skills:

Excellent communications skills and interpersonal skills
Possess high taste level
Ability to work in an open floor plan and remain focused on priorities
Highly organized and detail oriented
Flexibility to work long hours when necessary, high level of dedication
Strong collaboration and cross functional partnership skills
Strong organizational skills
Excel and Photoshop

It is the policy of PVH Corp. to ensure equal employment opportunities to all qualified persons without regard to race, gender, religion, age, national origin, citizenship status, disability, qualified veteran status, marital status, or sexual orientation.
