PVH Corp.


Manager Product Development - Tommy Hilfiger in
            
New York, New York








If you are a current PVH Associate, please click this link to apply through your Workday account.  at https://www.myworkday.com/pvh
Design Your Future at PVH
Manager Product Development - Tommy Hilfiger
Responsibilities

Daily communication with overseas offices and factories on all product details, delivery requirements, costing, and purchase orders.  Ensure that all details are accurately updated in a timely manner and conveyed to appropriate parties.
Costing
Review historical costing to determine targets
Analyze, negotiate and confirm costing from factories
Create and maintain cost logs in DTS
Weekly analysis of deliveries by vendor
Execution and distribution of allocation chart for proto and bulk production.
Determine sample and bulk allocations based on shipping history, performance and capability.
Maintain seasonal development and bulk calendars with overseas partners.
Filter and liaison all production issues  from overseas vendors to design and merchandising counterparts
Daily communication with overseas counterparts
Attend fittings to ensure that any delv and/or cost issues that arise are addressed.
Seasonal line reviews with Customs and FTC
Attend adoption, proto and weekly CFT meetings
Issue bulk purchase orders via system; double-check via buy/PO/allocated to make sure PO matches bought quantity
Delivery tracking: Update the revised at consolidator dates daily; implement delivery policy; make sure all late deliveries have comments explaining delay; clean up overages and shortages
Monitor PTR report – Delivery/Log fit samples with tech; Meet weekly with tech dept; Make sure fit samples are sent in a timely fashion
Track all samples, salesman to TOP samples

QUALIFICATIONS

5 years’ experience in product development
College Degree or relevant business experience
Attention to detail
Strong follow through skills
Excellent communication skills – oral and written
Takes initiative
Can work independently
Strong PC Skills (MS Office, including Excel), MS Outlook
Ability to learn custom computer system

It is the policy of PVH Corp. to ensure equal employment opportunities to all qualified persons without regard to race, gender, religion, age, national origin, citizenship status, disability, qualified veteran status, marital status, or sexual orientation.
http://www.pvh.com  at http://www.pvh.com/
Continue exploring our current job opportunities and take the next step towards designing your future.  at https://pvh.wd1.myworkdayjobs.com/PVH_Careers/jobs
With a history going back over 135 years, PVH has excelled at growing brands and businesses with rich American heritages, becoming one of the largest global apparel companies.
We are over 35,000 associates operating in over 40 countries and $8.2 billion in 2016 annual revenues. We own and market the iconic CALVIN KLEIN, Tommy Hilfiger, Van Heusen, IZOD, Arrow, Speedo*, Warner's, and Olga brands and, in addition, market a variety of goods under our own and licensed brands.
*The  Speedo  brand is licensed for North America and the Caribbean in perpetuity from  Speedo  International, Ltd.









